      "author_association": "MEMBER",
      "body": "I wonder if this tool ever found a real true positive, given that we are running it at confidence=100%, which can only find very limited things? Sure, dead code in tests isn't ideal and possibly scary, but if this only finds the plain obvious cases, that are unlikely to be written, and trivial to catch during manual review, maybe it could be removed?\n\nNo strong opinion, just wondering. In the meantime, I've submitted https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/pull/34814",
